JOHANNESBURG – South African Airways (SAA) CEO Vuyani Jarana and the airline's board have walked out of Parliament, refusing to deliver a scheduled presentation. Jarana was meant to present a turnaround strategy for the airline on Wednesday. READ: Turbulence ahead as SAA records massive loss The SAA delegation wanted a closed meeting, but MPs objected, citing a lack of transparency. Closed meetings in Parliament are unusual. eNCA